<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE53489053D6FEEFFAE2" box="[160,330,1274,1298]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plates 126D, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE53496553D6FE13FAE2" box="[341,438,1274,1298]" captionStart="PLATE 127" captionStartId="406.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1400,224,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-113@406.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="406" captionText="PLATE 127. A. Mesosoma. B. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum. C, D, F–H. Chelae. E. Head. A, C. Gonatopus daunus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, D. G. fyanensis (=G. magnus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. hainanensis, holotype (E from Olmi 2003; F from Olmi 1986). G. G. iarensis (=G. bouceki), holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H. G. javanus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.20 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 0.31 mm for F, 0.26 mm for G and 0.22 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278818/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">127A, C</figureCitation>
