<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FDDFE5348A752A9FE2BF8BD" pageId="403" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FDDFE5348A752A9FD92F8D9" blockId="403.[151,1436,1413,2014]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FDDFE5348A752A9FE00FA6D" bold="true" box="[151,421,1413,1438]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FDDFE534A4752A9FCA4FA6D" box="[631,769,1413,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="403" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous-reddish, except petiole black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:4:11:7:6.5:6:6:5:5:6. Head (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534BC05285FB36FA31" box="[1008,1171,1449,1473]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126D, E</figureCitation>
) dull, granulated, with temple very prominent and occiput very excavated; frontal line incomplete; occipital carina incomplete, shortly present only behind posterior ocelli; POL = 1; OL = 3; OOL = 6.5. Palpal formula 5/2. Pronotum shiny, unsculptured, with lateral regions longitudinally striate, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, sculptured by some longitudinal striae. Metanotum transversely striate, hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE5349185171FE03F985" box="[296,422,1629,1653]" captionStart="PLATE 127" captionStartId="406.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1400,224,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-113@406.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="406" captionText="PLATE 127. A. Mesosoma. B. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum. C, D, F–H. Chelae. E. Head. A, C. Gonatopus daunus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, D. G. fyanensis (=G. magnus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. hainanensis, holotype (E from Olmi 2003; F from Olmi 1986). G. G. iarensis (=G. bouceki), holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H. G. javanus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.20 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 0.31 mm for F, 0.26 mm for G and 0.22 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278818/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 127A</figureCitation>
) shiny, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface without transverse striae; anterior surface very inclined, with deep median longitudinal furrow. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 12:3:4:13:21. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE53497851E5FE61F911" box="[328,452,1737,1761]" captionStart="PLATE 127" captionStartId="406.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1400,224,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-113@406.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="406" captionText="PLATE 127. A. Mesosoma. B. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum. C, D, F–H. Chelae. E. Head. A, C. Gonatopus daunus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, D. G. fyanensis (=G. magnus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. hainanensis, holotype (E from Olmi 2003; F from Olmi 1986). G. G. iarensis (=G. bouceki), holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H. G. javanus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.20 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 0.31 mm for F, 0.26 mm for G and 0.22 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278818/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 127C</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and seven peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534D5451E5FF76F8F5" captionStart="PLATE 127" captionStartId="406.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[200,1400,224,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-113@406.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="406" captionText="PLATE 127. A. Mesosoma. B. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum. C, D, F–H. Chelae. E. Head. A, C. Gonatopus daunus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, D. G. fyanensis (=G. magnus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. hainanensis, holotype (E from Olmi 2003; F from Olmi 1986). G. G. iarensis (=G. bouceki), holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H. G. javanus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.20 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 0.31 mm for F, 0.26 mm for G and 0.22 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278818/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 127C</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally not serrated, with two rows of four (proximal) + 18 lamellae; distal apex with about 13 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FDDFE5348F75019FE2BF8BD" blockId="403.[151,1436,1413,2014]" box="[199,398,1845,1869]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FDDFE5348F75019FEAEF8BD" bold="true" box="[199,267,1845,1869]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Male.</emphasis>
